    "extract": "Red Robin Gourmet Burgers, Inc., more commonly known as Red Robin Gourmet Burgers and Brews or simply Red Robin, and formerly known as Sam's Tavern, and then Sam's Red Robin before the name change to Red Robin Gourmet Burgers and Brews and an industry switch to hamburgers in 1969. It is an American chain of casual dining restaurants originally founded in 1940 in Seattle, Washington. In 1979, the first franchised Red Robin restaurant was opened in Yakima, Washington. Red Robin's headquarters is in Greenwood Village, Colorado. As of December 2024, the company operated a total of 498 restaurants,"
